The paper deals with decoding of block codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of syndrome polynomials and iterative error reduction also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of iterative decoding (cs.ITP). The paper also discusses the use of reliability measures and information set decoding, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI), respectively. Finally, the paper specifically mentions cyclic codes, which are a sub-class of error-correcting codes (cs.CC).
